//1. what is virtual dom - optional

Virtual dom is a lightweight copy of the real dom. 
It is a node tree that lists the elements, their attributes and content as Objects and their properties. 
It is a programming concept where an ideal, or “virtual”, representation of a UI is kept in memory and synced with the “real” DOM by a library such as ReactDOM. 
This process is called reconciliation.

//2. how react renders dom in conservative manner - optional

React uses a virtual DOM (a JavaScript representation of the real DOM). 